Breaking News | American Airlines Facing Wrongful Death Lawsuit
Breaking News | American Airlines Facing Wrongful Death Lawsuit

American Airlines is facing a wrongful death lawsuit from the family of a woman who died after suffering a medical emergency during a flight two years ago. According to NBC Dallas, 25-year-old Brittany Oswell was on American Flight 102 from Honolulu to Dallas when she suffered an embolism that’s caused her to lose consciousness in the onboard lavatory.
